 Chloe the wombat , who first made headlines after her special bond with her surrogate zookeeper mum emerged last December , has found herself a new buddy at Taronga Zoo 's grounds in Sydney after she moved into her new digs alongside a couple of echidnas .
In an adorable video uploaded to Instagram by Taronga , Chloe is seen trying to take a nap in the mud on one of the echidna .
Chloe likes to follows her zoo keeper Evelyn Weston around the zoo .